During Ramadan, Muslims must fast from sunup to sundown, withstanding at least 16 hours without food or water. featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Kallapalli is situated on a high ground on the bank of Mayyazhi River and has to climb 44 steps to reach the top. The church remains in its old form. Small developments have come. It was a major trading center during the British/French/Dutch era. There is a large cemetery attached to it. A large madrasa can also be seen. Ashaikh May'Alawi bin Ba'alawi (ra) is laid to rest here. It has come across the sea for the purpose of Islamic preaching. Kallapally Urus is held on Rabiul Awwal 6. People of all castes, religions and creeds come and join to fulfill their dreams.
It is a place of natural beauty that gives peace of mind. In Khabarstan we can see an ecosystem, Mayyazhi river is getting polluted day by day.
